request.description:
Submit a JSON array of recipients. Each object must contain:
- `address` — a valid Stellar G-address (56 chars, valid checksum)
- `amount`  — a decimal string (max 7 decimal places)

**Expected 200 response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "valid": [
      { "address": "GAAZI4...", "amountStroops": "1005000000" },
      { "address": "GBVVJJ...", "amountStroops": "2001234567" },
      { "address": "GDQOE2...", "amountStroops": "500000000" }
    ],
    "errors": [],
    "totalRows": 3
  }
}
```

Demonstrates partial validation. Invalid rows are collected in the `errors` array; valid rows are still returned in `valid`. The third row has 8 decimal places (exceeds the 7-decimal stroop limit) and will also appear in `errors`.

**Expected 200 response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "valid": [
      { "address": "GAAZI4...", "amountStroops": "1005000000" }
    ],
    "errors": [
      { "row": 2, "address": "INVALID_ADDRESS", "reason": "Invalid G-address checksum" },
      { "row": 3, "address": "GBVVJJ...", "reason": "Amount exceeds 7 decimal places" }
    ],
    "totalRows": 3
  }
}
```

response.body:
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "valid": [
      { "address": "GAAZI4TCR3TY5OJHCTJC2A4QSY6CJWJH5IAJTGKIN2ER7LBNVKOCCWN", "amountStroops": "1005000000" }
